f3CfmMIB.description: This module defines the CFM (8021AG) Extension MIB definitions used by the F3 (FSP150CM/CC) product lines. Copyright (C) ADVA Optical Networking.

CfmAisGenTriggerTypes.name: CfmAisGenTriggerTypes
CfmAisGenTriggerTypes.description: Bit Mask that specifies all the defects that can trigger AIS to be generated.

CfmAisInterval.name: CfmAisInterval
CfmAisInterval.description: AIS interval which is the frequency of ETH-AIS frame generation. Note the values of the 1 second and 1 minute integers which are aligned with the values defined for the AIS interval for AIS PDU in Y.1731.

CfmLmmDmmInterval.name: CfmLmmDmmInterval
CfmLmmDmmInterval.description: Y.1731 Loss or delay measurement frame transmission interval.

CfmMepDefects.name: CfmMepDefects
CfmMepDefects.description: A MEP can detect and report a number of defects such as RDI, MACStatus, RMEP CCM, Error CCM, Xconn CCM. These are are defined in Dot1agCfmMepDefects in standard 802.1ag MIB. Y.1731 adds additional defects such as AIS defect which is defined here. bDefAIS(0) A MEP received an ETH-AIS frame/indication.

CfmLLFTriggerTypes.name: CfmLLFTriggerTypes
CfmLLFTriggerTypes.description: Bit Mask that specifies all the conditions that trigger a link loss forwarding.

CfmSignalFailTriggers.name: CfmSignalFailTriggers
CfmSignalFailTriggers.description: Bit Mask that specifies all the conditions that trigger Signal Fail.

CfmSlmEnabledTypes.name: CfmSlmEnabledTypes
CfmSlmEnabledTypes.description: Bit Mask that specifies all the priorities.

cfmEthType.name: cfmEthType
cfmEthType.description: This object provides the system level Ethernet type for CFM.

cfmMacAddress.name: cfmMacAddress
cfmMacAddress.description: This object provides the system level Mac address for CFM.

slmMulticastMacAddress.name: slmMulticastMacAddress

slmOpcode.name: slmOpcode
slmOpcode.description: This object can be used to configure the Operation Code for the Synthetic Loss Measurement(SLM) message.

slrOpcode.name: slrOpcode
slrOpcode.description: This object can be used to configure the Operation Code for the Synthetic Loss Response(SLR) message.

cfmSignalFailTriggers.name: cfmSignalFailTriggers
cfmSignalFailTriggers.description: This object can be used to configure the list of defects which constitute Signal Fail condition.

cfmMepTable.name: cfmMepTable
cfmMepTable.description: Additional MEP configuration such as Y.1731 configuration.

cfmMepEntry.name: cfmMepEntry
cfmMepEntry.description: A list of additional MEP parameters such the Y.1731 parameters.

cfmMepAdminState.name: cfmMepAdminState
cfmMepAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the CFM MEPs.

cfmMepAisGenTriggerTypes.name: cfmMepAisGenTriggerTypes
cfmMepAisGenTriggerTypes.description: A bit mask which indicates all the defects that result in triggering an AIS for the higher level MEP or transmission of ETH-AIS.

cfmMepAisClientMdLevel.name: cfmMepAisClientMdLevel
cfmMepAisClientMdLevel.description: AIS Client MD level which is the MD level used to identify any higher level local MEPs for which AIS defect needs to be set or MD level of the ETH-AIS frame generated if there are no local MEPs at this MD level.

cfmMepAisInterval.name: cfmMepAisInterval
cfmMepAisInterval.description: ETH-AIS frame transmission interval if decision is made to transmit the ETH-AIS frame.

cfmMepAisGenEnabled.name: cfmMepAisGenEnabled
cfmMepAisGenEnabled.description: This flag enables/disables propagation of ETH-AIS to client MD levels.

cfmMepAisPriority.name: cfmMepAisPriority
cfmMepAisPriority.description: This VLAN priority of the ETH-AIS frame.

cfmMepLmTxCountAllPriosEnabled.name: cfmMepLmTxCountAllPriosEnabled
cfmMepLmTxCountAllPriosEnabled.description: This attribute is used when Y.1731 probes are created and LMM frames are transmitted. As per Y.1731, loss measurement should be done per priority class. The implementation is restricted to support counting of frames for only one priority that can be modified. As an added value there is an option to count all priorities. This flag is used to decide whether to put cumulative data frame counts for all the priorities into the LMM that is transmitted by the MEP instead of data frame counts for a provisioned individual priority.

cfmMepLmRxCountAllPriosEnabled.name: cfmMepLmRxCountAllPriosEnabled
cfmMepLmRxCountAllPriosEnabled.description: This attribute is used when Y.1731 probes are created and LMR frames are transmitted. As per Y.1731, loss measurement should be done per priority class. The implementation is restricted to support counting of frames for only one priority that can be modified. As an added value there is an option to count all priorities. This flag is used to decide whether to put cumulative data frame counts for all the priorities into the LMR that is transmitted by the MEP instead of data frame counts for a provisioned individual priority. LMR is sent by a MEP when an LMM is received.

cfmMepLmDualEndedCountAllPriosEnabled.name: cfmMepLmDualEndedCountAllPriosEnabled
cfmMepLmDualEndedCountAllPriosEnabled.description: This attribute is used when Y.1731 probes are created and CCM frames are transmitted with loss measurement counts. As per Y.1731, loss measurement should be done per priority class. The implementation is restricted to support counting of frames for only one priority that can be modified. As an added value there is an option to count all priorities. This flag is used to decide whether to put cumulative data frame counts for all the priorities into the CCM instead of data frame counts for a provisioned individual priority.

cfmMepLmCountInProfileEnabled.name: cfmMepLmCountInProfileEnabled
cfmMepLmCountInProfileEnabled.description: As per the Y.1731 data frames counted for loss measurement shall be in-profile (green) data frames. As an added value, this flag is provided for the device to count all frames instead of green frames only. This flag could be set to false in cases where the remote device is not color aware and/or capable of color marking. Even if the device is capable of color marking and is color aware if the outer tag is not an S-TAG it makes sense to set this flag to false. As defined in IEEE 802.1ad the S-TAG has the drop eligibility bit that is used to mark the frames green or yellow.

cfmMepLmTxPriority.name: cfmMepLmTxPriority
cfmMepLmTxPriority.description: This attribute is used if cfmMepLmTxCountAllPrios is false. This attribute serves three purposes: - It is the VLAN priority of the LMM. - Data frames transmitted and received with this VLAN priority are counted by the MEP. The transmit count is sent in the LMM and the receive count is used to complete the list of four counts used for the loss measurement. - If an LMR is received with a VLAN priority other than this the LMR is dropped.

cfmMepDmPriority.name: cfmMepDmPriority
cfmMepDmPriority.description: This attribute specifies the DMM frame VLAN priority.

cfmMepRxCCMs.name: cfmMepRxCCMs
cfmMepRxCCMs.description: This provides the total number of received CCMs on the MEP.

cfmMepErrCCMs.name: cfmMepErrCCMs
cfmMepErrCCMs.description: This provides the total number of errored CCMs on the MEP.

cfmMepLLFTriggerTypes.name: cfmMepLLFTriggerTypes
cfmMepLLFTriggerTypes.description: This bit mask indicates the CFM triggers that result in link loss forwarding.

cfmMepDefects.name: cfmMepDefects
cfmMepDefects.description: This bit mask indicates defects that not defined in standard 802.1ag MIB such as AIS defect.

cfmMepTagEtherType.name: cfmMepTagEtherType
cfmMepTagEtherType.description: This object allows management of Ether Type for MEP VLAN Tag for the MEPs.

cfmMepStatsAction.name: cfmMepStatsAction
cfmMepStatsAction.description: Allows the Manager to clear the CFM level statistics : cfmMepRxCCMs, cfmMepErrCCMs.

cfmMepOperationalState.name: cfmMepOperationalState
cfmMepOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the CFM MEP.

cfmMepSecondaryState.name: cfmMepSecondaryState
cfmMepSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the CFM MEP.

cfmMepSlmEnabled.name: cfmMepSlmEnabled
cfmMepSlmEnabled.description: This bit mask indicates the whether SLM is enabled per each COS.

cfmMepAssociatedObject.name: cfmMepAssociatedObject
cfmMepAssociatedObject.description: This object represents the associated port, it could be port, flow or flow point.

cfmAccPortQosShaperCIR.name: cfmAccPortQosShaperCIR

cfmAccPortQosShaperBufSize.name: cfmAccPortQosShaperBufSize

cfmAccPortQosShaperAdminState.name: cfmAccPortQosShaperAdminState

cfmNetPortQosShaperCIR.name: cfmNetPortQosShaperCIR
cfmNetPortQosShaperCIR.description: This object identifies the queue CIR.

cfmNetPortQosShaperBufSize.name: cfmNetPortQosShaperBufSize
cfmNetPortQosShaperBufSize.description: This object identifies the queue buffer size.

cfmNetPortQosShaperAdminState.name: cfmNetPortQosShaperAdminState

cfmServerMepEntry.name: cfmServerMepEntry
cfmServerMepEntry.description: This allows management of Server MEPs.

cfmServerMepIndex.name: cfmServerMepIndex
cfmServerMepIndex.description: The integer index value corresponding to a Server MEP.

cfmServerMepAssociatedPort.name: cfmServerMepAssociatedPort
cfmServerMepAssociatedPort.description: This is the port on which the CFM Server MEP is created.

cfmServerMepAisClientMdLevel.name: cfmServerMepAisClientMdLevel
cfmServerMepAisClientMdLevel.description: AIS Client MD level which is the MD level used to identify any higher level local MEPs for which AIS defect needs to be set or MD level of the ETH-AIS frame generated if there are no local MEPs at this MD level.

cfmServerMepAisInterval.name: cfmServerMepAisInterval

cfmServerMepAisGenEnabled.name: cfmServerMepAisGenEnabled
cfmServerMepAisGenEnabled.description: This flag enables/disables propagation of ETH-AIS to client MD levels.

cfmServerMepAisPriority.name: cfmServerMepAisPriority
cfmServerMepAisPriority.description: This VLAN priority of the ETH-AIS frame.

cfmServerMepStorageType.name: cfmServerMepStorageType
cfmServerMepStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

cfmServerMepRowStatus.name: cfmServerMepRowStatus
cfmServerMepRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of cfmServerMepRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with cfmServerMepRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The cfmServerMepRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

cfmServerMepAdminState.name: cfmServerMepAdminState
cfmServerMepAdminState.description: This object represents the Administrative State of the Server MEP.

cfmServerMepOperationalState.name: cfmServerMepOperationalState
cfmServerMepOperationalState.description: This object represents the Operational State of the Server MEP.

cfmServerMepSecondaryState.name: cfmServerMepSecondaryState
cfmServerMepSecondaryState.description: This object represents the Secondary State of the CFM MEP.

cfmDownMEPQosShaperTable.name: cfmDownMEPQosShaperTable
cfmDownMEPQosShaperTable.description: A list of configurable profile entries for CFM QoS Shapers for down MEPs.

cfmDownMEPQosShaperEntry.name: cfmDownMEPQosShaperEntry
cfmDownMEPQosShaperEntry.description: A list of parameters that set up the CFM QoS Queue profiles. This shaper is created automatically when the first Down MEP is created on a Port. Note, this queues is valid for port based Down MEPs, VID based down MEPs on NNI port.

cfmDownMEPQosShaperIndex.name: cfmDownMEPQosShaperIndex

cfmDownMEPQosShaperType.name: cfmDownMEPQosShaperType

cfmDownMEPQosShaperCIR.name: cfmDownMEPQosShaperCIR

cfmDownMEPQosShaperProfile.name: cfmDownMEPQosShaperProfile

cfmDownMEPQosShaperAdminState.name: cfmDownMEPQosShaperAdminState
cfmDownMEPQosShaperAdminState.description: This object allows the management of the Shaper Administrative State. Only 'in-service' and 'management' states are allowed.
